name: mcalf
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "mcalf" %}
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/mcalf-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 16cdf068a469e1c6edc743cce5dabbce694cd0bc36f480f7252850ca9fc5fb7b

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [py<36]
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools_scm
  run:
    - astropy >=4.2
    - matplotlib-base >=3.1
    - numpy >=1.18
    - pathos >=0.2.5
    - python
    - pyyaml >=5.1
    - scikit-learn >=0.22
    - scipy >=1.4

test:
  imports:
    - mcalf
    - mcalf.models
    - mcalf.profiles
    - mcalf.profiles.voigt
    - mcalf.profiles.gaussian
    - mcalf.utils
    - mcalf.utils.spec
    - mcalf.utils.smooth
    - mcalf.utils.mask
    - mcalf.utils.plot
    - mcalf.utils.misc
    - mcalf.visualisation
  commands:
    - pip check
    - python -c 'import platform;exit(0 if platform.python_implementation() == "PyPy" else 1)' || pytest --pyargs mcalf
  requires:
    - pip
    - pytest

about:
  home: https://github.com/ConorMacBride/mcalf/
  summary: 'MCALF: Multi-Component Atmospheric Line Fitting'
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.rst

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ConorMacBride
